column5: Walleye fishing off Port Maitland has been HOT ...Small Dipsys Back 250 plus on a 2 setting off the planner boards ...Big Dipsys of the corner of the boat 135 to 155 back on a 2 and 3 setting leave the down riggers in the garage they just spoke fish ...our team never runs riggers for walleye off Port Maitland ...get out there this weekend and chase those Walleye 72 to 82 fow ...   Best colors last weekend
My friend has pulled out many bows' from this end, including 2,15 pounders.
Awesome been doing Ontario lately for bows but looks like its time for some eyes 10miles out ?
